{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS","iPadOS","Mac Catalyst"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"readonly"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCoordinateBounds","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@MLNCoordinateBounds","text":"MLNCoordinateBounds"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}],"languages":["occ"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This property contains the smallest rectangle that completely encompasses the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"overlay. Implementers of this protocol must set this area when implementing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their overlay class, and after setting it, you must not change it."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If this overlay spans the antimeridian, its bounds may extend west of −180 degrees"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"longitude or east of 180 degrees longitude. For example, an overlay covering the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Pacific Ocean from Tokyo to San Francisco might have a bounds extending"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from (35.68476, −220.24257) to (37.78428, −122.41310)."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"}],"externalID":"c:objc(pl)MLNOverlay(py)overlayBounds","symbolKind":"property","title":"overlayBounds","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property","fragments":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/overlayBounds":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds","title":"overlayBounds","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type":"topic","title":"MapLibre","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNCoordinateBounds":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCoordinateBounds","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlncoordinatebounds","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNCoordinateBounds"}],"type":"topic","title":"MLNCoordinateBounds","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A rectangular area as measured on a two-dimensional map projection."}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol defines a specific type of annotation that represents"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"both a point and an area on a map. Overlay objects are essentially data objects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that contain the geographic data needed to represent the map area. Overlays can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"take the form of a polyline or polygon."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","fragments":[{"text":"MLNOverlay","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"MLNOverlay","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay","role":"symbol"}}}